cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.LG

The paper deals with the decidability of the first-order theory of graphs generated by trace rewriting systems with level-regular contexts. This involves concepts from logic (first-order theory), automata theory (finite concurrent automata), and graph theory (rewriting graphs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with the concurrent unfolding of finite concurrent automata, which falls under the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of graphs and their properties makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with regular languages, which falls under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper deals with the decidability of the first-order theory of graphs, which falls under cs.LG (Computational Geometry).
